  "Old yield = $4.80 / $120 = 4%. New yield = $4.80 / $96 = 5%. When a stock's price falls but the dividend remains the same, the yield increases because you get the same dollar amount on a cheaper share.": "",
  "The NASDAQ is known for listing major technology companies. If NASDAQ-listed tech stocks fall 25% from their recent high while non-tech stocks only fall 10%, what type of market condition exists for the NASDAQ?": "",
